UPSERT finding:doc_docs_per_object_quad_spec_md_there_is_a_sibling_cluster_at_0x8c26aa54_object SET statement='There is a sibling cluster at 0x8C26AA54 (object-pool base per re-catalog/00-README.md, referenced by bank04:11748). [INFERRED] a later routine (the TA submit / bulk-DMA, likely bank04) walks these tables and ships each object\'s quad list to the PVR TA FIFO. The draw routines themselves do no SQ / 0x10000000 writes (confirmed — no store-queue writes in loc_8c033d78/loc_8c033e90), so submission is ', status='confirmed', confidence='doc', source_file='docs/PER-OBJECT-QUAD-SPEC.md', section='1c. The two parallel result tables (CONFIRMED addresses, consumer INFERRED)';
