UPSERT finding:doc_memory_reference_mvc2_wire_gaps_md_hit_flash_trigger_confirmed_via_the_live_probe SET statement='Hit-flash trigger CONFIRMED via the live probe = char+0x275 ("0xff when in hitstun", pl_mem.asm:262) — found by stepping the field-stepper, NOT the disassembly (0x12e/0x40 were both flat). BUT 0x275 is GENERIC (fires on any hit, both characters) — it\'s only the body-flash trigger, not the electric. The electric is ATTACKER-specific: ship the attacker\'s DamageType (attack record +0x05) / Hitspark (', status='confirmed', confidence='doc', source_file='memory/reference_mvc2_wire_gaps.md', section='';
