UPSERT finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_gfx_data_00_425kb_u32_le_offset_table_firs SET statement='- GFX_DATA_00 (425KB): u32 LE offset table (first ptr/4 = 1533 entries) → variable-length (10–2535B) sprite pieces. Piece header decoded: [w_tiles][h_tiles][padded_w][padded_h] where padded = round-up-to-power-of-2; px size = w_tiles8 × h_tiles8. Then bytes [4][5][6] = per-piece sub-header (b5 often 00; b6 ∈ {05,07,0F}) followed by a transparency-aware 4bpp stream (palette idx 0 = transparent is w', status='confirmed', confidence='doc', source_file='memory/reference_pldat_sprite_format.md', section='';
RELATE finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_gfx_data_00_425kb_u32_le_offset_table_firs->cites->source:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md;
UPSERT finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_decision_don_t_reverse_the_rle_use_the_emulat SET statement='DECISION: don\'t reverse the RLE — use the emulator as the decompressor. Headless flycast already decodes every sprite into VRAM deterministically and we already hook the texture cache (the RAM-diff path). Offline "asset bake": script flycast through every char×animation, dump decoded textures + sprite_id→texture+palette map → client preload pack. Pixel-perfect by construction, zero codec RE, reuse', status='inferred', confidence='doc', source_file='memory/reference_pldat_sprite_format.md', section='';
RELATE finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_decision_don_t_reverse_the_rle_use_the_emulat->cites->source:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md;
UPSERT finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_live_test_validated_the_rom_asset_client_2026_0 SET statement='LIVE TEST VALIDATED the ROM-asset client (2026-06-04, branch feat/rom-asset-probe). Added env-gated MAPLECAST_STATELOG per-frame CSV dump in serverPublish (read-only, before wire work; commit 613f81385) + scripts/analyze-statelog.py. Captured a real Ryu(char_id 0 = PL00 ✓) vs Cable(23) match, 33s/1991 frames. Findings: (1) WORKING SET small/bounded — 90 unique sprite_ids for Ryu, 110 for Cable, ~2', status='confirmed', confidence='doc', source_file='memory/reference_pldat_sprite_format.md', section='';
RELATE finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_live_test_validated_the_rom_asset_client_2026_0->cites->source:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md;
UPSERT finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_pixel_level_verification_passed_2026_06_04_bran SET statement='PIXEL-LEVEL VERIFICATION PASSED 2026-06-04 (branch feat/rom-asset-probe). Built a WebGPU sprite-bake harness: web/webgpu/bake.mjs + hooks in web/webgpu-test.html (?ws= to connect direct to local mirror server; ?v= cache-bust). It consumes the server\'s GSTA state broadcast (char_id/sprite_id/screen_x,y at RAM 0xE0/0xE4), renders TRANSLUCENT-ONLY (drop opaque+punch — clean char isolation, no stage/H', status='confirmed', confidence='doc', source_file='memory/reference_pldat_sprite_format.md', section='';
