UPSERT finding:doc_memory_reference_pldat_sprite_format_md_why_it_matters_unlocks_option_6_rom_asset_cli SET statement='Why it matters: unlocks Option 6 / ROM-asset client — character layer becomes ~8B/slot (frame_index+x,y+pal+facing) vs ~230KB TA keyframes. Deterministic by construction (pure data lookup over already-byte-deterministic RAM state — see [[reference_determinism_validated]]), so the risk is PVR blend fidelity, not drift. Caveats: GFX codec unsolved; stages/projectiles/supers/effects live in separate ', status='confirmed', confidence='doc', source_file='memory/reference_pldat_sprite_format.md', section='';
